⭐ Checkstyle
	• Checks coding style and formatting.
	• Detects: 
		○ Naming issues
		○ Wrong indentation
		○ Line length violations
		○ Brace formatting
		○ Javadoc issues
	• Purpose: Keep code consistent, readable, and standardised.

⭐ SpotBugs (FindBugs)
	• Analyzes compiled bytecode.
	• Finds real runtime bugs.
	• Detects: 
		○ Possible NullPointerExceptions
		○ Wrong equals/hashCode
		○ Thread-safety issues
		○ Dead stores
	• Purpose: Improve correctness and prevent crashes.

⭐ Where They Are Used
	• Maven and Gradle builds
	• Jenkins/GitHub Actions CI pipelines
	• IntelliJ / Eclipse IDEs

⭐ Why They Are Important
	• Catch errors early
	• Reduce debugging time
	• Maintain quality and consistency
	• Avoid production bugs
	• Easier code reviews

⭐ Ultra‑Short Memory Trick
	• PMD → Bad coding practices
	• Checkstyle → Style and formatting
	• SpotBugs → Actual bugs in bytecode

