Docker host networking removes network isolation and allows a container to share the host’s network stack directly.
When you use the host network driver:
	• Docker does NOT create a virtual network interface for the container
	• Docker does NOT assign a separate IP address to the container
	• The container shares the host’s IP address
	• The container can see all host network interfaces

Docker none network completely disables networking for a container, providing maximum isolation.
• ✅ none network disables networking completely
• ✅ No IP address is assigned
• ✅ Only loopback interface is present
• ✅ Highest level of isolation
• ✅ Used for security‑critical workloads

• -p publishes specific ports from container to host
• -P publishes all exposed container ports to random host ports

