What is an Azure Region?
An Azure Region is a geographical location where Microsoft has one or more datacenters.
Examples:
	• Central India
	• East US
	• West Europe
Each region is physically separated from other regions by hundreds of kilometers.


✅ What is an Availability Zone?
An Availability Zone is a physically separate datacenter inside a region.
Each zone has:
	• Independent power
	• Independent cooling
	• Independent network
Most regions have 3 zones:
	• Zone 1
	• Zone 2
	• Zone 3

✅ What problem does a Zone solve?
✔ Protects against datacenter failure
✔ Provides High Availability (HA)
✔ Keeps app running during local failures

What is an Availability Set?
An Availability Set is a logical grouping of VMs within a single datacenter to protect against:
	• Hardware failures
	• Planned maintenance
It works using:
	• Fault Domains → different hardware racks
	• Update Domains → different maintenance windows

✅ What problem does a Set solve?
✔ Protects against server / rack failure
✔ Protects during Azure maintenance
❌ Does NOT protect against datacenter failure


